    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-21T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="149"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11010: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-21T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 21, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 21—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>600. Following from American Consul [General] at Shanghai: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 15, 3 p.m. In vicinity of Soochow, Standard Oil Company launch <hi
                                rend="italic">Mei Foo II</hi> was held up by bandits on July 9 at 6
                            p.m. and all that was worth while was looted. One foreigner received
                            slight injury but was permitted to continue. Chinese authorities have
                            been requested to make investigation and punish those guilty of the
                            offense and to take such precautionary measures as are necessary to
                            protect life in this large commercial district. This incident is
                            reported to the Legation as illustrating degree of protection which is
                            afforded by National Government in the district where it has undisputed
                            control. The bandits threaten that should the incident be given
                            publicity <pb facs="0247" n="149" xml:id="pg_149"/> through the press
                            all Standard Oil Company boats will be captured when plying between
                            Shanghai and Soochow.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
